@startuml component-grammar-registry-planned
'' ============================================================================
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: this shows a registry ATOM fed from two
'' sources (compile-time bundled base64 + a user config directory), validated by
'' clojure.spec, with the whole feature «planned». PlantUML's reusable dashed
'' <<planned>> stereotype marks every node Forthcoming uniformly; the filesystem
'' tan and DataScript-purple (registry = stateful single owner) colors keep
'' their fixed palette meaning. Mermaid lacks reusable stereotypes + record nodes.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Grammar registry (Forthcoming / «planned») — bundled + user grammars [Strategy/Interpreter]

rectangle "registry atom\n(name → grammar config)" as REG <<planned>> {
  card "{ :rholang {…} :metta {…}\n  :markdown {…} … }\nvalidated by clojure.spec\n(:grammar/name :wasm :highlights\n :extensions :scope)" as ATOMBODY
}

rectangle "bundled grammars\n(compile-time)" as BUNDLED #9F8766 {
  component "embed-base64\n<name>.wasm + highlights.scm\n→ inlined into the build" as EMBED <<planned>>
}

rectangle "user grammars\n~/.config/vinary-viewer/grammars/" as USER #9F8766 {
  component "<name>.wasm\n+ highlights.scm\n+ config map (.edn)" as USERFILES <<planned>>
}

rectangle "consumer" as CONS #2D9574 {
  component "source-view\nresolve grammar by\nfile extension / scope" as RESOLVE <<planned>>
}

EMBED     -[#999999,dashed,thickness=2]-> REG : (1) register bundled\n(base names: Rholang, MeTTa, …)
USERFILES -[#999999,dashed,thickness=2]-> REG : (2) main scans the dir,\nsends configs over IPC →\nregister at startup
REG       -[#2D9574,dashed,thickness=2]-> RESOLVE : (3) lookup by extension\n→ {:wasm :highlights}

note bottom of REG
  A **user** can teach vinary-viewer a new language without rebuilding: drop a
  compiled `.wasm`, a `highlights.scm`, and an `.edn` config into the grammars
  directory. clojure.spec validates each config before it enters the atom, so a
  malformed entry is rejected rather than corrupting the registry.
end note

legend right
  |= color/style |= concept |
  | <#9F8766> | grammar source (bundled asset / user config dir) |
  | <#A45BAD> | registry = single stateful owner (the atom) |
  | <#2D9574> | renderer consumer (source-view) |
  | dashed grey <<planned>> | NOT yet built (Forthcoming) |
endlegend
@enduml
